reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Difficult to put together and is wobbly
reviews.reviewText: I've put a LOT of furniture together. This was the most difficult piece I've put together. The pieces barely barely fit together and it was very difficult to get them to fit. I had to keep going back and almost completely unscrewing previous steps to try and get the pieces to fit together. It was a massive headache and my temper kept flaring.It is a VERY small table and chairs, but it fits a small space well. My friend who is 6 feet looks like a giant in the chair, but I, on the other hand, and 5'1" and it fits pretty well. The table is cheap quality and wobbles but it will do for a college apartment or very small space.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute but order of assembly is incorrect.
reviews.reviewText: Ok. It’s really cute. The assembly instructions are not in a logical order however. My recommendation, do step 5 first (backrest assembly of chair). Then set the backrest to the side. There is nothing about this step that touches any other step. Then do Step 4 (chair seat plate assembly). Wood plate is predrilled and the wood seat plate doesn’t bend. It’s easier to attach the legs without the metal backside. Then do Step 3 - attach the backrest assembly to the chair plate assembly. The fit will be tight and snug. But nothing that can’t be easily handled. And no need for the backrest top to get scratched up as you try to get the entire chair upside down as you screw it into place which is awkward.Yes it’s doable. I’m disabled and put this chair and table set together alone. As for the table ignore their steps.Attach the wine rack/shelf to the legs loosely and then the table top to the legs securely. Flip it over and add the lower cross sections then tighten the shelf and lower sections.I recommend doing the chairs first so you have a place to sit and rest IF like me, you require rest along the way.Happy assembly!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Tiny set perfect for a studio
reviews.reviewText: Tiny table and chair set perfect for a studio apt. That's about the size.It is not very well made, the chairs are actually uncomfortable to sit on..Thankfully I knew all this before buying because the size was the biggest consideration for me and I'm not dissapointed with that aspect of the product.

While the table and chairs were small as I wanted for this area, all is well as long as you don’t lean in the back of a chair to reach something that has fallen to the ground. The chair back is bound to collapse and you will go down with it. Otherwise the quality is fine for the price and they all clean up well. The seats are quite small and a purchase of 2 round 14” cushions goes a long way. Amazons option is quite pricy for this size of cushion, but I’m sure that you can find something suitable for less.. I would just recommend some padding as the seats are certainly hard in their own. A hidden shelf under the table has found to be s great place to hind trays.

reviews.reviewTitle: デザイン、サイズも丁度いい感じ
reviews.reviewText: 単人、夫婦２人なら、いいサイズだと思います。狭いスペースでは、軽くて華奢な作りがとてもいい。今回は梱包状態も良く破損や不良パーツはありませんでした。写真と同じ、組み立てに苦労したけど、すごく良かったですこの価格で買えて良かったです。
